\"The Dragon and the Pearl.\"] ''Metropolitan Museum Journal'', Vol. 26. (1991), pp 139&ndash;146. \n*Nischer, E. C. [https://www.jstor.org/stable/295741 \"The Army Reforms of Diocletian and Constantine and Their Modifications up to the Time of the Notitia Dignitatum.\"] ''The Journal of Roman Studies'', Vol. 13. (1923), pp 1&ndash;55. \n*Thompson, E. A. ''The Visigoths in the Time of Ulfila''. Oxford: Oxford University Press, 1966. \n*[[Herwig Wolfram|Wolfram, Herwig]]. ''History of the Goths''. Thomas J. Dunlap, trans. Berkeley: University of California Press, 1988.\n{{refend}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* Riders of the [http://www.comitatus.net/cavalrytaifali.html Comitatus] [[historical reenactment]] and [[living history]] group portray members of the late Roman ''Equites Honoriani Taifali seniores'' in northern England\n\n[[Category:Early Germanic peoples]]\n[[Category:Migration Period]]\n[[Category:Late Roman military units]]\n[[Category:Romania in the Early Middle Ages]]\n[[Category:History of the North Caucasus]]\n[[Category:Dacia]]\n[[Category:Military units and formations established in the 4th century]]\n", "name_user": "Srnec", "label": "safe", "comment": "don't need these", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taifals"}
